"James L. Williams Res., 1843 & 1859; has been turned around.  E. L. Armbruster Collection 1937"

"This house stood in the early 40's and for many years at the junction of Jamaica and Flatbush Roads or at Fulton Street and East New York Ave., facing Jamaica Ave."--Brooklyn's Eastern District,
by E. L. Armbruster, 1942, p. 341.
